" <div class=\"graphic\">",
"  <div class=\"figure\" style=\"width: 518px\">",
"   <div class=\"ttl\">",
"    Intracardiac electrograms during atrial tachycardia",
"   </div>",
"   <div class=\"cntnt\" style=\"width: 498px; height: 366px; background-image: url(data:image/jpeg;base64,);\">",
"   </div>",
"   <div class=\"lgnd\">",
"    Shown are surface ECG leads I, II, III, V1, and V6 and intracardiac electrograms form the right ventricular apex (RVA), ablation catheter (AC), and bundle of His (HBE). The AC is located at the site of earliest atrial activity during the tachycardia; the onset of the atrial electrogram at this site (dash line), which is fractionated and prolonged, precedes the onset of the P wave by 35 msec.",
"    <div class=\"footnotes\">",
